spahni@cui.unige.ch writes:
>Assuming that compressing a text means also diffusing the information, is
>it true that the encryption of a compressed text is harder to break than
>the same encryption of a non compressed text ?

In theory, that's true.  In practice, programs like PKZIP or the UNIX
compress command add known plaintext in the form of a header.

